org.parboiled.matchers
Class CustomMatcher

java.lang.Object
  org.parboiled.trees.ImmutableGraphNode<Matcher>
      org.parboiled.matchers.AbstractMatcher
          org.parboiled.matchers.CustomMatcher
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, Matcher, Rule, GraphNode<Matcher>
public abstract class CustomMatcher
extends AbstractMatcher

Base class of custom matcher implementations. If you want to implement custom matchers they have to be derived from this class. Instances of derived classes can be directly used in rule defining expressions. Caution: For performance reasons the parsing engine delegates the task of taking and restoring value stack snapshots to the matchers. Your custom matcher implementations therefore have to take care of value stack managment themselves! (See the implementation of the SequenceMatcher for hints on how to do this!)
